https://media1.s-nbcnews.com/i/videoassets/ndp/latest/ndp-hls.js
  e.prototype = Object.create({
    constructor: e
  }, {
    getID: {
      value: function() {
        return this.id
      },
      enumerable: !0
    },

    getName: {
      value: function() {
        return this.name
      },
      enumerable: !0
    },
    getURL: {
      value: function() {
        return this.url
      },
      enumerable: !0
    },
    getCC: {
      value: function() {
        return this.cc
      },
      enumerable: !0
    },
    isLive: {
      value: function() {
        return this.isLiveMedia
      },
      enumerable: !0
    },
    getVideoData: {
      value: function() {
        var t = this.getURL(),
          e = t.indexOf("?") > 0 ? "&" : "?",
          n = {};
        return n.url = t + e + "format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4", n.cc = this.getCC(), n
      },
      enumerable: !0
    },
    assetTypes: {
      get: function() {
        return {
          fire: ["fireTvOnceStreaming", "FireTV-Once"],
          akamai: ["akamaiMp4", "Akamai Video"],
          limelight: ["limelightMp4", "Limelight MP4"],
          once: ["unicornOnceStreaming", "OnceURL"],
          hls: ["liveHls", "Live HLS"],
          hds: ["liveHds", "Live HDS"]
        }
      }
    }
  })

inference (attempt #1):
=======================
  * URL to .SMILE (XML) for highest bitrate @ 1080p
      http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true
  * URL to HLS
      http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4
  * test:
      curl 'http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4' --insecure --include
    result:
      Location: https://snappytvpoc-pmd.nbcuni.com/media/video/NBC_News_Digital/2021/11/1638116216646_mtp_netcast_211128_6.mp4?
    outcome:
      interesting; the URL derived from the "videoAsset" for any particular MP4 resolution results in a 302 redirect to the MP4 video file.. without requiring the download and parsing of an intermediate .SMILE (XML) file

inference (attempt #2):
=======================
  * URL to .SMILE (XML) for highest bitrate @ 1080p
      http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true
  * URL to HLS
      http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&manifest=m3u&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4
  * test:
      curl 'http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&manifest=m3u&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4' --insecure --include
    result:
      Location: https://snappytvpoc-vh.akamaihd.net/i/media/video/NBC_News_Digital/2021/11/1638116216646_mtp_netcast_211128_,6,5,4,3,2,1,.mp4.csmil/master.m3u8?__b__=1000
    outcome:
      success; the URL derived from any "videoAsset" resolution results in a 302 redirect to an adaptive master HLS manifest with all available bitrate streams (ex: 1..6)
    compatability:
      plays in:
       - Clappr (web browser)
       - Chromecast
      does not play in:
       - ExoPlayer (Android)
    what to do?
      might be better to list all available formats:
       - MP4 @ various resolutions
       - HLS @ adaptive bitrate

sample filter (all available episodes):

{
  var data   = JSON.parse( window.document.querySelector('script#__NEXT_DATA__').innerText )
  var videos = data.props.initialState.video.current.associatedVideoPlaylist.videos || data.props.initialState.video.associatedPlaylists[0].videos

  // preprocess list of videos

  videos = videos.map(function(video){
    return {
      url:         video.url.canonical,
      title:       video.headline.primary,
      description: video.description.primary,
      videos:      {
        mp4:       video.videoAssets.map(function(asset){
                      return {
                        bitrate: asset.bitrate,
                        width:   asset.width,
                        height:  asset.height,
                        url:     asset.publicUrl + '&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4' + '#video.mp4'
                      }
                   }),
        hls:       video.videoAssets[0].publicUrl + '&format=redirect&manifest=m3u&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4' + '#video.m3u8'
      },
      duration:    video.videoAssets[0].assetDuration * 1000,
      date:        (new Date(video.datePublished)).toLocaleDateString(),
      caption_url: video.closedCaptioning.webvtt || video.closedCaptioning.srt || video.closedCaptioning.smptett || ''
    }
  })

  console.log(videos.length)
  console.log(JSON.stringify(videos, null, 2))
}

sample filter (current episode only):
=====================================
{
  var data   = JSON.parse( window.document.querySelector('script#__NEXT_DATA__').innerText )
  var videos = [data.props.initialState.video.current]

  // preprocess list of videos

  videos = videos.map(function(video){
    return {
      url:         video.url.canonical,
      title:       video.headline.primary,
      description: video.description.primary,
      videos:      {
        mp4:       video.videoAssets.map(function(asset){
                      return {
                        bitrate: asset.bitrate,
                        width:   asset.width,
                        height:  asset.height,
                        url:     asset.publicUrl + '&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4' + '#video.mp4'
                      }
                   }),
        hls:       video.videoAssets[0].publicUrl + '&format=redirect&manifest=m3u&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4' + '#video.m3u8'
      },
      duration:    video.videoAssets[0].assetDuration * 1000,
      date:        (new Date(video.datePublished)).toLocaleDateString(),
      caption_url: video.closedCaptioning.webvtt || video.closedCaptioning.srt || video.closedCaptioning.smptett || ''
    }
  })

  console.log(videos.length)
  console.log(JSON.stringify(videos, null, 2))
}

compatability (update):
=======================
  * ExoPlayer:
    - HTTP fails to play
      * most likely the result of a security policy
        - preventing a 302 redirect from HTTP to HTTPS
      * examples..
        - mp4:
            http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4#video.mp4
        - hls:
            http://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&manifest=m3u&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4#video.m3u8
    - HTTPS works
      * examples..
        - mp4:
            https://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4#video.mp4
        - hls:
            https://link.theplatform.com/s/rksNhC/mhJmaj4Bg6ro?mbr=true&format=redirect&manifest=m3u&format=redirect&Tracking=true&Embedded=true&formats=MPEG4#video.m3u8

what to do? (update):
=====================
  * update all video URLs from HTTP to HTTPS

what to do? (optional):
=======================
  * only use adaptive HLS URL?
    - simplifies the UI and allows an automatic redirect when a video is detected
    - better to make this a configuration that the user can change
